correctness.rationale: Multiple factual and unit errors, plus many untraceable/fabricated values. Key issues: (1) Dosing/purge times use unit MilliSEC but numeric values are in seconds; should be converted to ms: DEZ dose 4000 ms (not 4), O2 dose 1500 ms (not 1.5), post-DEZ purge 4500 ms (not 4.5), post-O2 purge 500 ms (not 0.5). (2) Flow rates use unit SCM-PER-MIN but values are in sccm; convert to m^3/min: O2 60 sccm → 6.0e-5 m^3/min; Ar purge 80 sccm → 8.0e-5 m^3/min. The 160 value corresponds to the thermal ALD carrier gas (not PEALD) and should not be listed as precursorFlow for this PEALD process. (3) CarrierGas set to Ar is not explicitly reported for the PEALD cycle (only purge gas Ar is stated); mark as unreported or justify with text. (4) NucleationPeriod set to 0 cycles is not supported; the article notes a positive intercept but provides no cycle count. (5) NumberofCycles = 318 is derived from GPC and thickness and not reported explicitly; this harms traceability. (6) Material and device properties are populated with zeros/"Not Found" without support: optical properties (RI, absorption, band gap), electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, mobility), uniformity variation, conformality aspect ratio, elemental concentration and 1:1 atomic ratio, film density, and all TFT device metrics—none are reported for the PEALD films; these should be omitted or left unreported rather than set to 0. Electrical resistivity for PEALD was stated as too high to measure, not 0. (7) Roughness value 6.3 nm (AFM) is not clearly supported; Table I indicates 6.5 (150 °C) and unit inconsistencies (Å vs nm); this needs correction and precise citation. (8) SupercycleDesign with count 1 is speculative and not reported. Correct/Remove the above and retain only values traceable to text: method (PEALD), DEZ/O2 plasma, substrate, reactor (Genitech MP-1000, shower-head), pressure 3 Torr (~3 mmHg), temperature range/150 °C case, RF power 60 W, O2 flow 60 sccm, Ar purge 80 sccm, GPC 2.2 Å/cycle, thickness ~70 nm, polycrystalline by XRD with (002) preference at 150 °C.

completeness.rationale: Several critical omissions and inconsistencies. (1) Multiple processes in the article are not represented: only one PEALD process at 150 °C/60 W is extracted, while the paper also reports PEALD at 75 and 100 °C (all at 60 W), PEALD at 150 °C with rf power varied (60, 100, 150 W), and a comparison ALD using H2O co-reactant (with reported electrical properties). Each should be a separate process instance; the H2O-based ALD process is entirely missing. (2) Many values are untraceable or incorrect: dosing/purge times are given with unit MilliSEC but numeric values are seconds (4.0, 1.5, 4.5, 0.5) — they must be converted to ms (4000, 1500, 4500, 500). NucleationPeriod is set to 0 cycles without support; numberOfCycles (318) is inferred and not stated in the text (traceability issue). PrecursorFlow 160 sccm is taken from the H2O-ALD description and not reported for the PEALD process; its inclusion here is likely incorrect. Roughness 6.3 nm corresponds to 100 °C, not the 150 °C PEALD process (which is ~6.5 nm), and 150 °C (water) roughness ~29 nm is also reported but not captured. (3) Many schema-required material properties are filled with placeholder zeros or fabricated values: optical properties, uniformity, conformality, elemental concentration and atomic ratio (set to 1:1), film density, device properties, and otherAspects flags (“False”) are not supported by the article. Electrical properties are reported in the article for the H2O-ALD film (ρ = 1.85 Ω·cm; μ = 23.8 cm²/V·s) and “too high to measure” for PEALD, but the extraction records zeros/Not Found. (4) SupercycleDesign is included though the process is binary and no supercycles are described. To improve completeness, add distinct processes for: PEALD at 75, 100, 150 °C (60 W) with correct roughness values and GPC trend; PEALD at 150 °C with rf = 100 and 150 W; and the H2O-based ALD process (including 4 s DEZ, 2.5 s H2O, 4.5 s purge, Ar 160 sccm, reported resistivity and mobility). Correct units for all times, remove/adjust untraceable placeholders (uniformity, conformality, composition, density, device metrics, stability/reproducibility), and align roughness and flow values to the appropriate process conditions.
